Antony Carelli, founding member of S.P.A.C.E. and one of the four individuals serving on its Board of Governors, was born Antony Leonardo Vincenzo Guillermo Carelli on January 2, 2007 in Naples, Italy to Leonardo and Roberta Carelli.
Carelli inherited a vast fortune from his parents at their untimely death in a small-ship crash in 2034. He began investing in multiple space ventures soon afterward upon coming into control of The Space Program itself. Carelli lives with his wife Carolina in Paris, France.
